cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with authorship attribution, which is a natural language processing task, indicating that it could belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The use of complex network approach and visualization techniques suggest that it could also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The use of principal component analysis and comparison with chance baseline method suggest that it could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of mesoscopic representation of texts suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL). Finally, the use of network analysis to capture the flow of narrative suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
